# Scenario 2: DevSecOps User & Department Access Configuration

**Author:** Naomi Onwuka  
**Date:** 21/02/2026  
**Purpose:** Demonstrate Linux user creation, department-based grouping, privilege management, 
CI/CD service account setup, and user removal with home directory preservation.

Part A: Create Department Groups
## Step 1: Create Groups

sudo groupadd dev_team
sudo groupadd sec_team
sudo groupadd qa_team

# Screenshot







# Create users (without password for one)
sudo useradd lateef
sudo useradd arthur
sudo useradd purity
sudo useradd habiba
sudo useradd paula
sudo useradd yaa
sudo useradd alex
sudo useradd aminat
sudo useradd ci_runner -s /usr/sbin/nologin  # service account


# Assign users to groups
sudo usermod -aG dev_team lateef
sudo usermod -aG dev_team arthur
sudo usermod -aG sec_team purity
sudo usermod -aG sec_team habiba
sudo usermod -aG qa_team paula
sudo usermod -aG qa_team yaa
sudo usermod -aG ops_team alex
sudo usermod -aG ops_team aminat

# Screenshot

## Step 3: Set Password for One User

# Timestamp
date
# Example output: Wed Feb 21 10:10:30 UTC 2026

# Set password for lateef (created without password)
sudo passwd lateef

# Confirm password updated
sudo grep lateef /etc/shadow
# Output example: lateef:$6$abcd1234...:18295:0:99999:7:::

